Author:  MORRIS
Vol / Page:  462
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Taawhiri,</i> or <i>Tawiri, n.</i> Maori name for the <i>Black Mapau.</i> A name applied to the tree <i>Pittosporum tenuifolium, N.O. Pittosporeae. </i>It is profusely covered with a fragrant white blossom. See <i>Mapau</i>. [1872 Domett]; 1884 Bracken
